The paper deals with algorithms for computing vertex separators in graphs with treewidth k = O(\sqrt[3]n), which is a topic in graph theory and graph algorithms. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions an application of the algorithm to solve monadic second-order problems, which falls under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The algorithm presented in the paper has a time complexity of c^k n(log^* n) log log n, which suggests that it may be relevant to cs.CG (Computational Geometry) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the paper deals with space-efficient algorithms, which could be relevant to cs.DL (Digital Libraries).
